dcterms:description: The EMDNA dataset provides daily precipitation and temperature data at a resolution of 0.1 degrees, which is used to calculate long-term average climatic attributes influencing water table depth.
dcterms:title: EMDNA dataset

dcterms:creator: J. T. Abatzoglou

dcterms:description: The TerraClimate dataset provides long-term average values of potential evapotranspiration, actual evapotranspiration, and maximum snow water equivalent at a resolution of 0.04 degrees.
dcterms:title: TerraClimate dataset

dcterms:creator: B. Tozer

dcterms:description: The SRTM15+ dataset provides global bathymetry and topography data at a resolution of 15 arc seconds, which is used to analyze topographic influences on water table depth.
dcterms:title: SRTM15+ dataset

dcterms:creator: L. Daac
dcterms:description: The GTOPO30 dataset is a global 30 arc-second elevation data set used to analyze topographic influences on water table depth.
dcterms:title: GTOPO30 dataset

dcterms:description: The Soilgrids dataset provides high-resolution soil property maps for various depths and soil layers, which are used to characterize hydraulic properties influencing water table depth.
dcterms:title: Soilgrids dataset

dcterms:description: The MODIS Land Cover Dynamics Product (MCD12Q) provides global land cover and phenology metrics at 500-meter spatial resolution, which are used to analyze land cover influences on water table depth.
dcterms:title: MODIS Land Cover Dynamics Product (MCD12Q)
